WEBVTT

00:00:41.437 --> 00:00:42.647
I mean…

00:00:46.734 --> 00:00:48.653
Let's not say anything for now.

00:00:50.780 --> 00:00:54.450
I can't say that it was a mistake,
that we should pretend…

00:00:57.954 --> 00:00:59.539
it never happened.

00:01:08.590 --> 00:01:10.592
Because it wasn't a mistake.

00:01:20.602 --> 00:01:21.603
We're here.

00:01:28.526 --> 00:01:29.569
Wait.

00:01:33.740 --> 00:01:37.076
Here. It's the last day
of the exhibition tomorrow.

00:01:46.211 --> 00:01:47.295
I'll be waiting.

00:01:54.052 --> 00:01:55.011
Goodbye, then.

00:01:57.931 --> 00:01:58.765
Right.

00:03:31.649 --> 00:03:34.277
LEE KYU-TAE SOLO EXHIBITION

00:05:15.586 --> 00:05:17.588
Stay there. I'll come to you.

00:05:37.900 --> 00:05:38.901
Sorry I'm late.

00:05:38.985 --> 00:05:40.445
No, it's okay.

00:05:43.656 --> 00:05:44.574
That's…

00:05:46.576 --> 00:05:48.327
Let's hurry. We're gonna be late.

00:05:49.620 --> 00:05:50.455
Right.

00:06:02.383 --> 00:06:03.718
Why were you late?

00:06:05.094 --> 00:06:06.429
What matters is I'm here.

00:06:07.722 --> 00:06:08.890
Why are you here?

00:06:10.308 --> 00:06:11.893
EPISODE 9
LIKE OR LOVE

00:06:11.976 --> 00:06:13.311
To see you.

00:06:24.906 --> 00:06:25.823
Are you okay?

00:06:27.533 --> 00:06:29.619
Of course. I'm totally fine.

00:06:43.549 --> 00:06:44.634
Drink this.

00:06:51.015 --> 00:06:52.016
I'll protect you.

00:07:13.120 --> 00:07:14.372
Yellow? Really?

00:07:15.122 --> 00:07:15.957
It's pretty!

00:07:19.085 --> 00:07:20.211
The V sign?

00:07:20.294 --> 00:07:21.212
Come here.

00:07:33.933 --> 00:07:35.726
Ta-da. I'm good, aren't I?

00:07:44.110 --> 00:07:45.194
Are you okay?

00:07:45.278 --> 00:07:46.779
-I've got this.
-You've got this?

00:07:51.325 --> 00:07:53.494
There are five of us,
so we need three toppings.

00:07:53.578 --> 00:07:54.996
-Lovely.
-Two kinds of noodles.

00:07:55.079 --> 00:07:57.498
-And cheese. Make that two.
-Glass noodles.

00:07:57.582 --> 00:08:00.668
Order jjolmyeon noodles, too,
with a side of dumplings.

00:08:00.751 --> 00:08:02.086
-Awesome.
-Love it!

00:08:03.045 --> 00:08:04.046
Let's eat by ourselves.

00:08:05.673 --> 00:08:06.674
Sounds good.

00:08:09.468 --> 00:08:10.803
Ta-da.

00:08:11.596 --> 00:08:13.556
Okay. Ta-da!

00:08:14.473 --> 00:08:15.891
That's so cute.

00:08:20.605 --> 00:08:22.481
How is it? Isn't it good?

00:08:25.318 --> 00:08:26.777
It's delicious.

00:08:27.862 --> 00:08:29.447
Let me try one.

00:08:29.530 --> 00:08:33.200
Why don't you try the pork cutlet first?
You shouldn't…

00:08:42.585 --> 00:08:44.337
It's way too salty. Are you okay?

00:08:44.420 --> 00:08:46.422
-I love it. Really.
-No. Don't eat it.

00:08:53.304 --> 00:08:54.305
Sounds delicious.

00:09:08.736 --> 00:09:09.612
Thank you.

00:09:10.112 --> 00:09:11.656
Here, let me pour you a drink.

00:09:20.414 --> 00:09:22.083
Two lids for two bottles!

00:09:23.209 --> 00:09:25.211
-I can handle just one glass.
-Whoa, no.

00:10:12.216 --> 00:10:16.595
Yes. For lunch,
I had tuna gimbap and jjolmyeon.

00:10:16.679 --> 00:10:17.513
My wrist?

00:10:18.097 --> 00:10:21.851
It's better than yesterday,
but I'm still struggling. Yeah.

00:10:22.476 --> 00:10:25.354
Okay. I'll call you back later.

00:10:27.815 --> 00:10:31.819
He calls me ten times a day.
You don't mind hearing us, do you?

00:10:32.445 --> 00:10:33.279
Of course not.

00:10:33.362 --> 00:10:35.030
He's far away right now, you see.

00:10:37.783 --> 00:10:40.202
-What is it?
-You look happy, that's all.

00:10:41.287 --> 00:10:42.955
Really? I do?

00:10:47.376 --> 00:10:49.628
Oh, right. I should wrap that up.

00:10:54.675 --> 00:10:58.262
We managed to sneak past his manager
out of the green room,

00:10:58.345 --> 00:11:00.097
but there were fans everywhere.

00:11:00.181 --> 00:11:02.516
I held my bias's hand and ran for it.

00:11:02.600 --> 00:11:05.811
We arrived at the parking lot,
but the fans were there too,

00:11:05.895 --> 00:11:09.982
so we ended up huddling down together
between the van and the wall.

00:11:10.065 --> 00:11:12.902
-I could hear his heart beating fast.
-Oh God.

00:11:13.402 --> 00:11:15.905
And with it, I could feel his warmth.

00:11:16.530 --> 00:11:17.531
And then…

00:11:18.157 --> 00:11:19.283
This is insane.

00:11:35.174 --> 00:11:36.550
Here?

00:11:38.636 --> 00:11:40.763
What? Is there a problem?

00:11:41.680 --> 00:11:43.432
No. There's no problem.

00:11:56.195 --> 00:11:58.656
Babe, wait.
What if my manager walks in on--

00:11:59.156 --> 00:11:59.990
Be quiet.

00:12:00.574 --> 00:12:02.034
Okay.

00:12:05.204 --> 00:12:06.539
Stay still.

00:12:25.182 --> 00:12:26.267
Stop.

00:12:26.350 --> 00:12:28.269
You… want to pick another one?

00:12:29.770 --> 00:12:30.980
Yes.

00:12:31.063 --> 00:12:32.815
Calm down a bit.

00:12:32.898 --> 00:12:37.486
Let's try just ten themes a week.

00:12:37.570 --> 00:12:39.572
How come? I have tons of free time.

00:12:41.323 --> 00:12:44.243
Well, at this rate,

00:12:44.743 --> 00:12:47.830
you'll have met all 900 of them
by next month.

00:12:47.913 --> 00:12:49.665
You know,

00:12:50.249 --> 00:12:52.084
I really like it here.

00:12:53.168 --> 00:12:54.169
I can see that.

00:12:54.253 --> 00:12:57.798
It's a massive dopamine boost.
My confidence is soaring.

00:12:58.465 --> 00:13:00.467
And no one here is calling me man-crazy,

00:13:00.551 --> 00:13:03.512
dissing me for not taking
my relationships seriously.

00:13:03.596 --> 00:13:05.347
I can just move on to the next guy.

00:13:06.807 --> 00:13:07.850
On top of all that,

00:13:07.933 --> 00:13:11.353
even when I try the themes
everyone else is having trouble with,

00:13:12.271 --> 00:13:14.690
I can clear them in one go.

00:13:15.357 --> 00:13:18.068
I really, really love that.

00:13:19.445 --> 00:13:21.447
Being overwhelmingly good at something.

00:13:22.031 --> 00:13:23.532
It's such a rush!

00:13:25.159 --> 00:13:27.411
Submit.

00:13:27.494 --> 00:13:28.537
THANK YOU

00:13:31.916 --> 00:13:35.377
BOYFRIEND ON DEMAND 178TH THEME REVIEW
THE GUY NEXT DOOR

00:13:35.920 --> 00:13:38.088
592 LIKES, 930 COMMENTS

00:13:38.672 --> 00:13:41.425
What's this?
Why are there so many comments?

00:13:41.926 --> 00:13:43.928
YOUR POST JUST HIT 10,000 VIEWS!

00:13:47.890 --> 00:13:49.642
Your post just hit 10,000 views!

00:13:49.725 --> 00:13:52.561
Wait, what is happening right now?

00:13:57.399 --> 00:14:00.903
Who put up all these decorations,
and when?

00:14:01.946 --> 00:14:02.988
I wonder.

00:14:03.072 --> 00:14:04.698
What are you doing for Seollal?

00:14:05.991 --> 00:14:08.953
Me? I'm just going to eat tangerines
and read comic books.

00:14:09.912 --> 00:14:12.748
My mom told me not to come over
since she's going on a trip,

00:14:12.831 --> 00:14:16.335
so I'll be rotting away at home
for five days.

00:14:16.418 --> 00:14:18.921
Well, all the better.
Take the chance to rest.

00:14:23.801 --> 00:14:25.469
He offered to help us with this.

00:14:27.680 --> 00:14:31.433
I'll put the tree in the storeroom later.
Should I start with this one?

00:14:31.517 --> 00:14:32.351
Yes.

00:14:34.895 --> 00:14:36.647
Do you have plans for the holidays?

00:14:36.730 --> 00:14:39.024
I'm going to read comic books
and eat tangerines.

00:14:39.775 --> 00:14:41.151
What?

00:14:52.162 --> 00:14:53.414
You guys really…

00:14:57.793 --> 00:15:01.213
Whatever am I gonna do about you nerds?

00:15:01.922 --> 00:15:04.925
You're reading comic books
in the age of OTT platforms?

00:15:05.009 --> 00:15:08.429
Mr. Hwang keeps calling me uncultured,
and it's all because of you guys.

00:15:08.512 --> 00:15:11.223
Stop reading them now.
You guys have read enough.

00:15:12.266 --> 00:15:14.935
I'll go put these in the archives.

00:15:26.697 --> 00:15:28.574
It's dangerous out there.

00:15:32.661 --> 00:15:34.830
What are you doing?
You can't follow me in here.

00:15:34.913 --> 00:15:37.249
What's wrong?
I'm only here to put this away.

00:15:37.332 --> 00:15:39.501
Hey! Then I'll go out first.

00:15:52.056 --> 00:15:53.057
Wait a second.

00:16:06.195 --> 00:16:08.739
-What if someone sees us?
-Just act natural.

00:16:08.822 --> 00:16:10.324
That's easier said than done.

00:16:11.408 --> 00:16:13.744
Man, I'm a terrible liar.

00:16:14.244 --> 00:16:16.080
The office life will be the death of me.

00:16:19.708 --> 00:16:21.043
Should we just get caught?

00:16:22.503 --> 00:16:23.587
You are insane.

00:16:45.943 --> 00:16:47.027
Sweetie.

00:16:50.906 --> 00:16:52.825
-Are you okay?
-Huh?

00:16:55.994 --> 00:16:56.829
I am okay.

00:17:05.879 --> 00:17:07.548
Having fun teasing me?

00:17:08.173 --> 00:17:09.299
What about dinner?

00:17:10.384 --> 00:17:13.387
I have a meeting with Ms. Yun.
Eat without me.

00:17:14.763 --> 00:17:16.348
I'll pick you up later.

00:17:26.525 --> 00:17:28.026
Order some food for me.

00:17:28.110 --> 00:17:30.571
My wrist is killing me!

00:17:31.071 --> 00:17:33.991
This industry overworks its authors
way too much.

00:17:34.074 --> 00:17:36.743
I'll reduce the number of panels
in my next contract.

00:17:37.244 --> 00:17:39.621
Soon, I won't even be able to
hold up a spoon.

00:17:39.705 --> 00:17:41.874
Yun Song's contract is almost up.

00:17:41.957 --> 00:17:44.918
At this rate, we'll never renew
the contract on good terms.

00:17:46.879 --> 00:17:50.716
Have you talked to Director Hwang
about your next contract yet?

00:17:51.425 --> 00:17:54.595
No. Come to think of it,
he hasn't mentioned it yet.

00:17:55.387 --> 00:17:56.388
I'm sure he will soon.

00:18:07.357 --> 00:18:10.611
Ms. Yun, if we wait until the next season,
it will be too late.

00:18:11.445 --> 00:18:12.863
Do you have a solution?

00:18:14.573 --> 00:18:17.826
Do you remember
when PlanC first joined us on Fridays?

00:18:18.410 --> 00:18:22.664
It's time for us to find out what's wrong
and make changes like we did then.

00:18:23.332 --> 00:18:25.918
This is something you need to do.

00:18:26.001 --> 00:18:28.754
There has to be something only you can do.

00:18:28.837 --> 00:18:29.671
Seo.

00:18:30.547 --> 00:18:32.090
Are you trying to dump it on me?

00:18:33.175 --> 00:18:36.345
It's not like that.
I'm also going to give it my all.

00:18:36.845 --> 00:18:41.516
But still, please don't forget
that this is your work.

00:18:51.610 --> 00:18:54.571
I just don't know anymore.
This is too difficult.

00:18:56.990 --> 00:18:58.408
Can I take a look?

00:18:59.493 --> 00:19:00.327
Sure.

00:19:04.581 --> 00:19:06.333
THE MAN TO KNOW
STORY DEVELOPMENT OUTLINE

00:19:07.501 --> 00:19:08.502
What do you think?

00:19:09.336 --> 00:19:11.838
It might catch attention
for a little while, but…

00:19:12.756 --> 00:19:13.757
But that's it, huh?

00:19:15.384 --> 00:19:16.385
Yes.

00:19:18.512 --> 00:19:20.180
This won't do at all.

00:19:21.807 --> 00:19:24.434
We need to get through this
if we want to beat PlanC.

00:19:25.727 --> 00:19:28.563
Stop looking. I've already shown
too much to my competition.

00:19:32.401 --> 00:19:33.235
Adorable.

00:19:34.695 --> 00:19:35.529
What?

00:19:36.446 --> 00:19:37.281
I mean,

00:19:38.282 --> 00:19:39.533
why are you so adorable?

00:19:42.160 --> 00:19:45.580
Hey now, that's no way to talk about
someone who's working hard.

00:19:45.664 --> 00:19:47.165
-Hmph.
-"Hey now"?

00:19:57.676 --> 00:20:01.263
Could you draw a picture for me too?
Like the one you gave to Hwany.

00:20:01.346 --> 00:20:02.180
Sure.

00:20:02.264 --> 00:20:04.266
Really? You mean it?

00:20:04.349 --> 00:20:05.183
Yes.

00:20:06.852 --> 00:20:08.854
Would you like me to draw you?

00:20:10.355 --> 00:20:11.189
What?

00:20:13.608 --> 00:20:14.860
Want me to draw you?

00:20:20.115 --> 00:20:21.199
You don't like that?

00:20:23.660 --> 00:20:25.078
No, I love it.

00:20:36.673 --> 00:20:39.009
This is something you need to do.

00:20:39.092 --> 00:20:41.011
There has to be something only you can do.

00:20:47.976 --> 00:20:49.227
Oh God, seriously.

00:20:49.770 --> 00:20:54.191
Why does everyone keep bitching at me?
For goodness' sake.

00:21:03.450 --> 00:21:06.536
Why does everyone keep bitching at me?

00:21:07.371 --> 00:21:10.957
I mean, everyone with a mouth
keeps spouting off at the author!

00:21:11.041 --> 00:21:12.376
Easy for them to say.

00:21:12.459 --> 00:21:15.170
I'd like to see them try.
They'd manage, what, three panels?

00:21:15.253 --> 00:21:18.256
No, not even a single panel,
and they keep giving me orders.

00:21:18.340 --> 00:21:22.636
I work hard, they say, "Make it fun."
I make it fun, they say, "Work faster."

00:21:22.719 --> 00:21:25.806
Damn it! It's so annoying, seriously!

00:21:37.651 --> 00:21:39.069
Going on another hiatus, then?

00:21:39.986 --> 00:21:42.906
No. I mean, I have to push through.

00:21:44.324 --> 00:21:46.576
So you don't put that producer
in a hard spot?

00:21:47.411 --> 00:21:48.495
It's not that, but…

00:21:49.830 --> 00:21:52.958
You know,
I just don't want to let her down.

00:21:54.668 --> 00:21:56.586
Why's that? Because she's your friend?

00:21:59.464 --> 00:22:02.759
You've got such a kind heart, Song.

00:22:03.468 --> 00:22:07.222
You're the only person who says I'm kind.

00:22:07.305 --> 00:22:09.516
People don't know
what they're talking about.

00:22:10.892 --> 00:22:11.810
I should get going.

00:22:12.394 --> 00:22:13.854
Huh? Where to?

00:22:13.937 --> 00:22:16.440
You should work hard
to not let your friend down,

00:22:16.523 --> 00:22:18.775
and I should help you get motivated.

00:22:19.693 --> 00:22:21.570
Come see me at my workplace in a bit.

00:22:30.245 --> 00:22:32.622
What's this? He told me to come here.

00:23:20.045 --> 00:23:21.421
Oh my!

00:23:23.924 --> 00:23:24.799
You're here.

00:23:26.343 --> 00:23:29.054
What's this? Hansel and Gretel?

00:23:31.181 --> 00:23:34.392
Nothing beats sweet treats
when you're feeling down.

00:23:35.519 --> 00:23:36.937
It seems to be working.

00:24:02.379 --> 00:24:04.381
HANDMADE TOFU RESTAURANT

00:24:07.175 --> 00:24:10.679
Why does this guy always tag along
when our team comes out to eat?

00:24:14.224 --> 00:24:17.352
Come on, Naemo's a small company.
We're all on the same team.

00:24:17.435 --> 00:24:19.521
Oh, right you are.

00:24:22.315 --> 00:24:23.900
This is a place where any romance…

00:24:23.984 --> 00:24:25.485
That ad is everywhere these days.

00:24:26.069 --> 00:24:27.904
There are 900 themes just for you.

00:24:27.988 --> 00:24:32.033
It's getting a ton of buzz right now,
so they are striking while the iron's hot.

00:24:32.909 --> 00:24:36.037
I think that's our real competition,
not the other webtoon platforms.

00:24:37.414 --> 00:24:39.207
Why would anyone use that anyway?

00:24:40.750 --> 00:24:42.043
What do you mean, why?

00:24:42.627 --> 00:24:45.839
What girl wouldn't want to date
an attractive guy?

00:24:46.339 --> 00:24:47.924
Are you a subscriber?

00:24:48.008 --> 00:24:50.135
-Just eat your food.
-Okay.

00:24:52.804 --> 00:24:55.890
So, who will you be dating today?

00:24:56.725 --> 00:24:58.935
It's been a while. Go for drinks?

00:24:59.019 --> 00:25:00.186
Seriously?

00:25:00.270 --> 00:25:02.606
Why even ask? We definitely should!

00:25:04.316 --> 00:25:07.736
What time do you finish work today?
Join us as soon as you can.

00:25:07.819 --> 00:25:10.405
I can't promise anything.
Ms. Yun is so unpredictable.

00:25:10.488 --> 00:25:12.282
Goodness, you poor thing.

00:25:12.782 --> 00:25:15.201
Kyeong-nam, you should come with us.

00:25:15.285 --> 00:25:18.288
I also have a deadline.
I should head back with her.

00:25:18.371 --> 00:25:20.707
How come?
Hwany's already submitted his work.

00:25:21.416 --> 00:25:23.501
-What?
-Look.

00:25:23.585 --> 00:25:26.588
Going home now! Enjoy today's episode!

00:25:30.133 --> 00:25:32.135
Since when did he post that kind of stuff?

00:25:35.221 --> 00:25:37.974
I guess that means
you can come with us, right?

00:25:38.058 --> 00:25:39.184
Call me when you finish.

00:25:39.267 --> 00:25:40.352
-Let's go!
-Let's go.

00:25:40.435 --> 00:25:41.353
Wait, I…

00:25:43.063 --> 00:25:43.897
I…

00:25:44.856 --> 00:25:46.650
To that place we went to last time.

00:25:46.733 --> 00:25:47.567
Okay!

00:25:55.617 --> 00:25:57.744
DON'T BE TOO LATE, BUT TAKE YOUR TIME!

00:25:59.412 --> 00:26:00.997
Maybe I pushed her too much.

00:26:09.506 --> 00:26:11.174
Seo Mi-rae!

00:26:18.556 --> 00:26:20.141
Seo Mi-rae!

00:26:21.142 --> 00:26:23.395
Did you hear something just now?

00:26:25.271 --> 00:26:26.398
Sorry?

00:26:26.940 --> 00:26:27.899
I didn't hear

00:26:28.942 --> 00:26:30.026
a thing.

00:26:30.110 --> 00:26:31.486
I see.

00:26:31.569 --> 00:26:32.904
Am I hearing things?

00:26:43.081 --> 00:26:44.582
Why did you come here?

00:26:44.666 --> 00:26:46.084
Wow, it's Seo Mi-rae.

00:26:46.167 --> 00:26:49.671
I put my finger on this thingy,
but it wouldn't open.

00:26:50.171 --> 00:26:52.590
-Thank God.
-It's supposed to open, right?

00:26:53.133 --> 00:26:55.802
How much did you drink?
Why are you so drunk?

00:27:01.808 --> 00:27:03.476
Enjoy.

00:27:06.229 --> 00:27:09.441
I've never seen anyone get drunk
and go home before the food is served.

00:27:09.524 --> 00:27:10.775
I know, right?

00:27:10.859 --> 00:27:13.445
Why did you offer him a drink
as soon as we got here?

00:27:13.528 --> 00:27:15.447
Who knew one glass would knock him out?

00:27:18.950 --> 00:27:21.202
I wonder if he got home safe.

00:27:39.095 --> 00:27:40.096
Oh God!

00:27:48.188 --> 00:27:49.147
I'm fine though.

00:27:49.230 --> 00:27:51.900
No. The fact that you came here
means you're not fine.

00:27:52.609 --> 00:27:55.069
What did you even tell the others
before you left?

00:27:56.237 --> 00:27:57.989
I told them I was heading home.

00:27:58.865 --> 00:27:59.866
You did well.

00:28:00.617 --> 00:28:03.203
Stay here until I finish my work, okay?

00:28:03.286 --> 00:28:04.621
So I did well?

00:28:05.288 --> 00:28:07.207
-Stay.
-Stay.

00:28:07.290 --> 00:28:09.459
-Stay.
-Stay.

00:28:16.174 --> 00:28:18.009
Hey. I'll be going home now.

00:28:18.092 --> 00:28:19.844
Sure. Good night.

00:28:23.807 --> 00:28:26.476
-Get home safe. See you tomorrow.
-Sure.

00:28:27.060 --> 00:28:29.145
-Good work today.
-Goodbye, then.

00:28:51.417 --> 00:28:54.003
Really? It's only ten o'clock.

00:29:18.361 --> 00:29:19.779
Have you sobered up a bit?

00:29:20.280 --> 00:29:22.991
You really shouldn't have come here.
That was so close.

00:29:23.658 --> 00:29:27.245
I'm sorry. I just missed you so much.

00:29:29.122 --> 00:29:31.833
Oh, you. You did well.

00:29:32.333 --> 00:29:33.668
Let's go now.

00:29:33.751 --> 00:29:36.754
Ms. Yun submitted her work early,
so I'm heading out.

00:29:46.472 --> 00:29:48.308
Did you match them up again?

00:29:48.391 --> 00:29:49.642
I think I might have.

00:29:49.726 --> 00:29:51.978
So how many did you match up today?

00:29:58.568 --> 00:30:00.904
I can go by myself.

00:30:00.987 --> 00:30:02.655
I should still walk you all the way.

00:30:03.156 --> 00:30:04.240
Okay, then.

00:30:08.620 --> 00:30:11.122
-Haven't you forgotten something?
-What do you mean?

00:30:13.458 --> 00:30:14.459
Just go already.

00:30:20.423 --> 00:30:21.257
Anything else?

00:30:22.634 --> 00:30:24.385
Keep that up, and I won't let you go.

00:30:37.565 --> 00:30:38.900
I'm home.

00:30:38.983 --> 00:30:42.028
I hereby forbid you from drinking
without me. See you tomorrow.

00:30:46.532 --> 00:30:47.367
See you tomorrow.

00:30:49.994 --> 00:30:53.623
Sheesh, he never sends me
so much as a heart.

00:30:59.253 --> 00:31:02.590
1: THE MAN TO KNOW
2: PLANC

00:31:07.011 --> 00:31:07.845
Hey.

00:31:08.388 --> 00:31:10.264
Ms. Yun, have you seen the rankings?

00:31:11.015 --> 00:31:12.934
Yes, I just saw.

00:31:13.017 --> 00:31:15.269
I'm exhausted after working all night.

00:31:15.353 --> 00:31:17.271
Our readers are loving it right now.

00:31:17.355 --> 00:31:19.190
I knew you could do it.

00:31:19.691 --> 00:31:23.361
But how did you even come up with
something like that at the perfect moment?

00:31:23.444 --> 00:31:26.406
A chef with a big heart
who's the polar opposite of Choi Si-woo

00:31:26.489 --> 00:31:27.907
as the second male lead.

00:31:27.991 --> 00:31:30.660
The hotel will make a great setup
for a love triangle.

00:31:30.743 --> 00:31:31.744
It just…

00:31:34.163 --> 00:31:35.581
came to me out of the blue.

00:31:36.082 --> 00:31:38.292
We all have those days to be grateful for.

00:31:39.043 --> 00:31:41.212
Well, I'm loving it.

00:31:41.713 --> 00:31:42.630
Glad to hear that.

00:31:42.714 --> 00:31:45.383
Enjoy the holidays.
Let's keep at it when we get back.

00:31:46.676 --> 00:31:47.510
Ms. Yun.

00:31:48.094 --> 00:31:51.014
I'm so glad to be working with you.

00:31:52.098 --> 00:31:53.516
Didn't expect that.

00:31:54.267 --> 00:31:56.060
Go to bed. I'm hanging up now.

00:31:56.144 --> 00:31:57.103
Okay. Good night.

00:32:02.900 --> 00:32:04.110
Awesome!

00:32:13.870 --> 00:32:14.871
Congratulations.

00:32:18.041 --> 00:32:19.292
Thank you.

00:32:22.045 --> 00:32:23.254
You've done well.

00:32:24.756 --> 00:32:25.757
What?

00:32:29.510 --> 00:32:32.180
What's up with him?
That heart emoji came out of nowhere.

00:32:36.809 --> 00:32:39.562
Everything is just perfect.

00:32:47.153 --> 00:32:49.322
Is it okay for me to be this happy?

00:33:07.340 --> 00:33:09.300
-Hey, so--
-What am I going to do?

00:33:09.884 --> 00:33:11.761
-Huh?
-What am I supposed to do?

00:33:15.014 --> 00:33:17.683
What do you mean? Just work hard.

00:33:18.476 --> 00:33:21.813
Damn it. You never have a game plan
for anything, ever.

00:33:21.896 --> 00:33:23.564
No author needs to have a game plan.

00:33:23.648 --> 00:33:27.318
Just have fun, work hard, and draw well.

00:33:27.401 --> 00:33:29.821
God, just forget I said anything.

00:33:34.200 --> 00:33:36.035
Why are you putting your coat on?

00:33:36.661 --> 00:33:37.495
Huh?

00:33:44.085 --> 00:33:46.504
Isn't it a bit chilly in here?

00:33:46.587 --> 00:33:48.214
Why are you being so weird?

00:33:49.382 --> 00:33:51.050
What do you mean?

00:33:51.134 --> 00:33:53.594
You've been fidgeting
like you need a bathroom break.

00:33:53.678 --> 00:33:54.971
Do you have somewhere to be?

00:33:55.888 --> 00:33:56.722
Huh?

00:34:01.894 --> 00:34:03.479
I have to leave before dinner.

00:34:03.563 --> 00:34:07.150
Come on! Such a buzzkill.
We finally found the time to hang out.

00:34:08.359 --> 00:34:11.863
I can't believe you used to go on
about him being a jerk.

00:34:11.946 --> 00:34:13.656
This is why I never believe you.

00:34:13.739 --> 00:34:16.325
Hey, that was, like, ages ago.

00:34:16.409 --> 00:34:18.536
It wasn't even that long ago.

00:34:22.290 --> 00:34:23.124
Hey, but really--

00:34:23.207 --> 00:34:24.292
You have to go soon?

00:34:25.001 --> 00:34:29.338
Don't worry. I'll let you off soon.
I'm busy too, you know.

00:34:30.339 --> 00:34:31.174
Why are you busy?

00:34:32.758 --> 00:34:35.428
-I also have a date.
-You said you were going home.

00:34:35.511 --> 00:34:37.430
That's right. An at-home date.

00:34:37.513 --> 00:34:40.600
You said you weren't dating,
and you're already having a guy over?

00:34:41.601 --> 00:34:42.852
I guess I am.

00:34:53.571 --> 00:34:55.990
Yeah, I think you should get a set today.

00:34:56.490 --> 00:34:57.325
What?

00:34:58.367 --> 00:35:00.369
Hey! I was just looking.

00:35:00.453 --> 00:35:02.622
The red one?
What do you think of that one?

00:35:04.207 --> 00:35:05.458
I'm good. Just hurry up.

00:35:05.541 --> 00:35:07.793
-I think it'll look good on you!
-Hurry up.

00:35:20.681 --> 00:35:22.016
A little late, huh? Sorry.

00:35:22.099 --> 00:35:23.142
Come on in.

00:35:26.520 --> 00:35:28.189
-You must be cold.
-First, a gift.

00:35:46.207 --> 00:35:47.041
Are you hungry?

00:35:48.626 --> 00:35:49.919
I'm good for now.

00:35:50.878 --> 00:35:52.880
Tell me if you get hungry.
I'll cook for you.

00:35:55.508 --> 00:35:58.177
No, you're the guest.
I should be the one to cook.

00:35:59.303 --> 00:36:02.056
I'll make you tteokguk.
I bought the ingredients.

00:36:03.307 --> 00:36:05.226
What? You know how to do that too?

00:36:07.687 --> 00:36:09.272
Man, I'm hungry.

00:36:16.946 --> 00:36:18.698
I don't want to age another year.

00:36:19.532 --> 00:36:21.284
Careful, I'm holding a knife.

00:36:22.702 --> 00:36:23.869
Fine.

00:36:34.922 --> 00:36:36.340
Then shall we eat later?

00:36:38.384 --> 00:36:39.385
Shall we?

00:38:37.586 --> 00:38:39.672
Sir, I think you should
take a look at this.

00:38:41.674 --> 00:38:43.384
CONQUERING BOD BY BOYFRIENDKILLER

00:38:43.467 --> 00:38:44.969
What am I looking at?

00:38:45.469 --> 00:38:48.139
Apparently, it's all the rage
among our subscribers.

00:38:48.222 --> 00:38:49.056
What is it?

00:38:49.140 --> 00:38:51.225
Basically, it's like a walkthrough.

00:38:51.308 --> 00:38:55.229
It seems the subscribers who had trouble
with their dates are really into it.

00:38:55.312 --> 00:38:57.648
But it's not a game.
Who needs a walkthrough?

00:38:58.149 --> 00:39:00.860
This user must be treating it like a game.

00:39:05.448 --> 00:39:06.532
Eun-ho.

00:39:07.950 --> 00:39:09.577
Do you have someone you like?

00:39:19.837 --> 00:39:24.175
There's only one thing we need to
keep in mind in Boyfriend on Demand.

00:39:24.258 --> 00:39:26.010
Want to try liking me?

00:39:31.098 --> 00:39:32.099
Sure.

00:39:32.183 --> 00:39:36.437
No matter how desirable a guy may be,
you are the star of the show.

00:39:44.737 --> 00:39:47.490
What do you think? Do you like it?

00:39:48.532 --> 00:39:49.700
Yes.

00:39:49.783 --> 00:39:52.119
I'll take the necklace,

00:39:52.203 --> 00:39:54.788
but can you throw in this hotel too?

00:39:55.831 --> 00:39:59.752
So you don't need to feel intimidated
just because he is a chaebol…

00:40:21.774 --> 00:40:22.775
Bang!

00:40:27.238 --> 00:40:30.074
…or nervous about him being an NIS agent.

00:40:30.157 --> 00:40:31.742
Are you okay?

00:40:50.719 --> 00:40:54.056
Ms. Lee Ji-yeon,
you have obtained a love triangle item.

00:40:54.139 --> 00:40:55.015
Oh my.

00:41:05.568 --> 00:41:07.987
Are you worried about two-timing?

00:41:09.029 --> 00:41:09.863
Well, don't be.

00:41:10.447 --> 00:41:13.659
Dating two men isn't that bad.
I've done a lot worse.

00:41:19.832 --> 00:41:22.501
So here's my recommendation.

00:41:22.585 --> 00:41:27.256
"At night, play the love triangle theme
and pop two items to end up with four…"

00:41:27.339 --> 00:41:28.966
Four? Four men?

00:41:29.049 --> 00:41:30.968
Who… Who is this person?

00:41:31.051 --> 00:41:32.094
We're investigating.

00:41:32.177 --> 00:41:34.013
This must be all she ever thinks about.

00:41:34.096 --> 00:41:36.015
A dating sim writer? Or a web novelist?

00:41:36.098 --> 00:41:39.435
If this kind of fast-paced dating
becomes a trend,

00:41:39.518 --> 00:41:41.770
the long-term subscription
will inevitably drop.

00:41:41.854 --> 00:41:44.398
She dated 220 men in two months?

00:41:45.399 --> 00:41:46.650
Is she out of her mind?

00:41:59.371 --> 00:42:00.205
What's this?

00:42:00.289 --> 00:42:02.750
Turns out I left one out
when I gave you those books.

00:42:02.833 --> 00:42:05.085
I'd been wondering about that. Thanks.

00:42:06.003 --> 00:42:08.297
I'll see you tonight.
I have a meeting to attend.

00:42:08.380 --> 00:42:09.214
Okay.

00:42:34.573 --> 00:42:35.991
-Ms. Seo.
-Huh?

00:42:36.075 --> 00:42:38.285
Yes. What is it?

00:42:38.369 --> 00:42:40.704
An article just came out.

00:42:40.788 --> 00:42:42.665
An article? What article?

00:42:42.748 --> 00:42:44.917
I think you need to see this right away.

00:42:50.923 --> 00:42:53.217
TMTK ACCUSED OF PLAGIARIZING
BOYFRIEND ON DEMAND

00:42:53.300 --> 00:42:56.053
Famous author Yun Song
has been caught up in another scandal.

00:42:56.136 --> 00:42:58.097
Several posts pointed out the similarities

00:42:58.180 --> 00:43:01.600
between a new male character
in her hit webtoon, The Man to Know,

00:43:01.684 --> 00:43:06.313
and a character from Boyfriend on Demand,
the dating subscription service.

00:43:06.397 --> 00:43:10.484
The allegations claim that
the character's stature, thick eyebrows,

00:43:10.567 --> 00:43:14.613
and occupation as a five-star hotel chef
all come together to make him

00:43:14.697 --> 00:43:17.616
a carbon copy of a character
from Boyfriend on Demand.

00:43:18.409 --> 00:43:19.952
This device is switched off.

00:43:20.744 --> 00:43:22.830
Is Ms. Yun not picking up?

00:43:22.913 --> 00:43:24.206
What are we going to do?

00:43:25.082 --> 00:43:26.083
-What's going on?
-Sir.

00:43:26.166 --> 00:43:28.585
-Hello?
-Hey, is what they're saying true?

00:43:28.669 --> 00:43:30.587
-I'll call them right now.
-Do it now!

00:43:30.671 --> 00:43:34.091
Call the reporters right now
and find out what happened.

00:43:34.174 --> 00:43:37.177
Hold on. Can anyone reach Yun Song?

00:43:37.261 --> 00:43:40.681
Has she really been on
this Boyfriend on Demand thing?

00:43:47.438 --> 00:43:48.814
FEELINGS ARE NOW A PRODUCT

00:43:48.897 --> 00:43:50.941
POPULAR WEBTOON AUTHOR YUN SONG UNDER FIRE

00:43:51.900 --> 00:43:54.486
Our birth rates are low as it is.
This is unacceptable.

00:43:54.570 --> 00:43:56.488
What's this got to do
with low birth rates?

00:43:56.572 --> 00:44:00.534
It's giving people such high standards
that they don't even want to date anymore.

00:44:00.617 --> 00:44:04.913
The subscription fee is so high.
It's left countless young people in debt.

00:44:04.997 --> 00:44:08.208
How do you afford the subscription?
Are your parents paying for you?

00:44:08.292 --> 00:44:10.210
-You're so pathetic.
-Pathetic?

00:44:10.294 --> 00:44:13.255
Goofing around in the virtual world.
I bet she's a total loser.

00:44:13.338 --> 00:44:14.423
Loser?

00:44:16.884 --> 00:44:18.719
You lousy little shits!

00:44:20.554 --> 00:44:21.388
Where is she?

00:44:22.848 --> 00:44:23.682
I don't know.

00:44:24.349 --> 00:44:27.603
I waited, thinking she might show up,
but she didn't.

00:44:28.771 --> 00:44:30.522
What are we going to do?

00:44:31.356 --> 00:44:33.817
It's going to be okay. Let me come inside.

00:44:59.885 --> 00:45:03.847
Are you kidding? So this was the boyfriend
she bragged about back then.

00:45:03.931 --> 00:45:05.265
I can't even…

00:45:05.933 --> 00:45:09.603
Didn't she get all preachy on us, saying
that our lives are duller than hers?

00:45:10.479 --> 00:45:13.440
Man, she turned out to be
one hell of a woman.

00:45:13.524 --> 00:45:15.484
That's what I call a poker face.

00:45:15.567 --> 00:45:17.903
-Did you even prepare for this meeting?
-Hey.

00:45:18.403 --> 00:45:20.656
Isn't this going to hurt So-yeong as well?

00:45:21.323 --> 00:45:23.408
I mean, think about it.

00:45:23.492 --> 00:45:27.496
If TMTK were to get cancelled,
So-yeong would end up jobless, right?

00:45:27.579 --> 00:45:29.540
Well, I guess that could happen.

00:45:30.749 --> 00:45:33.001
No, we can't let that happen. No way.

00:45:34.378 --> 00:45:35.254
Hey, don't do it.

00:45:35.337 --> 00:45:37.214
So-yeong, are you doing okay?

00:45:37.297 --> 00:45:41.301
If you find yourself in need of a new job,
I'll set you up with a good one.

00:45:41.385 --> 00:45:42.219
Don't send that.

00:45:42.302 --> 00:45:45.514
What on earth was she thinking?
How could she screw you over like this?

00:45:45.597 --> 00:45:47.850
Please get back to me.
I'm worried about you.

00:45:53.105 --> 00:45:55.357
She didn't screw me over. Got it?

00:45:55.440 --> 00:45:58.527
Besides, I'm also on Boyfriend on Demand,
so mind your own business!

00:45:58.610 --> 00:45:59.444
Huh?

00:46:00.195 --> 00:46:01.029
Kyeong-nam.

00:46:04.032 --> 00:46:06.118
God, I told you not to send it.

00:46:18.213 --> 00:46:19.047
Hello.

00:46:19.715 --> 00:46:20.841
Have you eaten?

00:46:22.801 --> 00:46:23.635
No.

00:46:25.512 --> 00:46:26.638
Where are you?

00:46:26.722 --> 00:46:28.390
At Ms. Yun's studio.

00:46:28.891 --> 00:46:32.728
So-yeong just left,
but I think I'll wait a little longer.

00:46:34.313 --> 00:46:36.565
She might show up late, after all.

00:46:39.610 --> 00:46:43.697
If you just got off work,
can you do me a favor?

00:46:43.780 --> 00:46:45.616
Of course. What is it?

00:46:46.116 --> 00:46:49.286
The thumb drive with our meeting notes
is at my place,

00:46:49.369 --> 00:46:51.371
and I want to check them right now.

00:46:51.455 --> 00:46:54.166
But I'm worried Ms. Yun might come here
while I'm away.

00:46:54.249 --> 00:46:59.212
I'm sorry, but could you go to my place
and send them to me?

00:47:00.005 --> 00:47:01.840
I'll head over right now.

00:47:01.924 --> 00:47:02.758
Thank you.

00:47:04.343 --> 00:47:06.511
I think I'll be home really late.

00:47:07.012 --> 00:47:09.181
But can you still wait for me?

00:47:10.432 --> 00:47:12.517
Sure. I'll see you later.

00:47:12.601 --> 00:47:13.518
See you.

00:47:40.170 --> 00:47:41.880
BOYFRIEND ON DEMAND

00:48:02.067 --> 00:48:03.527
Why would anyone use that anyway?

00:48:04.945 --> 00:48:06.196
BOYFRIEND ON DEMAND REVIEW

00:48:06.279 --> 00:48:08.782
TRIAL TIME: 50 HOURS
USER SATISFACTION SURVEY

00:48:14.037 --> 00:48:14.871
Damn it.

00:48:33.098 --> 00:48:34.266
Damn it. Come on!

00:48:44.192 --> 00:48:45.694
Why isn't he picking up?

00:48:51.700 --> 00:48:52.993
SEO MI-RAE

00:49:07.758 --> 00:49:09.217
Taxi!

00:49:12.387 --> 00:49:13.638
Yongsan, please.

00:49:16.266 --> 00:49:17.517
Pick up!

00:49:21.313 --> 00:49:22.731
8. REVIEW

00:49:40.332 --> 00:49:41.166
Damn it.

00:49:48.673 --> 00:49:49.508
Mi-rae.

00:49:52.469 --> 00:49:53.303
Why are you here?

00:49:53.970 --> 00:49:57.390
Well, your phone…
Why didn't you pick up your phone?

00:49:58.767 --> 00:50:00.102
I was busy cleaning.

00:50:11.321 --> 00:50:12.155
Are you all right?

00:50:15.450 --> 00:50:16.576
Thank you.

00:50:21.790 --> 00:50:22.707
Is something wrong?

00:50:24.543 --> 00:50:25.961
Is it because of Ms. Yun?

00:50:27.003 --> 00:50:28.004
No.

00:50:28.088 --> 00:50:29.798
Or did the director say something?

00:50:36.555 --> 00:50:38.640
Why did you race home? I'm worried.

00:50:43.395 --> 00:50:44.271
It's just that

00:50:45.939 --> 00:50:47.190
I was scared.

00:50:48.942 --> 00:50:50.026
Of what?

00:50:53.572 --> 00:50:54.447
Just

00:50:55.740 --> 00:50:57.325
scared of everything.

00:51:07.419 --> 00:51:09.254
I'm sure Ms. Yun will be okay.

00:51:11.923 --> 00:51:15.510
I can't tell him what I'm scared of.

00:51:16.469 --> 00:51:19.306
I just can't bring myself to tell him.

00:52:38.260 --> 00:52:39.427
When was this taken?

00:52:41.179 --> 00:52:42.430
She looks good in it.

00:52:47.644 --> 00:52:51.648
I WANTED TO TELL YOU THAT I LIKE YOU

00:52:59.531 --> 00:53:01.032
I was a little mad at you.

00:53:01.700 --> 00:53:04.703
For not even answering me
when I asked you to come with me.

00:53:05.996 --> 00:53:08.748
So I was just going to get over you, but

00:53:10.000 --> 00:53:11.334
it's harder than I thought.

00:53:12.585 --> 00:53:13.670
I miss you.

00:54:15.023 --> 00:54:16.024
Seo Mi-rae.

00:54:36.711 --> 00:54:37.837
What took you so long?

00:54:39.172 --> 00:54:40.006
What?

00:54:43.718 --> 00:54:44.636
How is this…

00:58:01.666 --> 00:58:06.671
Subtitle translation by: Daham Yoon